  <h1>
   gamepad_button_count
  </h1>
  This function will return the
  <i>
   total
  </i>
  number of buttons available for the gamepad connected to the given device "slot".
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">gamepad_button_count(device);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      device
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      Which gamepad device "slot" to check.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">b_num = gamepad_button_count(0);
</code></pre>
  The above code will return the number of buttons available on the gamepad plugged into device "slot" 0 and store the value in the variable "b_num".
 </body>
</html>